%N A395580 Number of axially symmetric tilings of an L-tromino of order n by elementary L-trominoes.
%C A395580 The L-tromino, also known as the chair, is a rep-tile.
%C A395580 The elementary L-tromino consists of three unit squares joined edge-to-edge to form an L-shape.
%C A395580 An L-tromino of order n is a scaled copy of the elementary L-tromino in which each square has side length n, where n is a positive integer.
%C A395580 The L-tromino is axially symmetric and admits axially symmetric tilings for each order n.
